<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Vault PKI Demo - Simplified</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        .vault-logo { color: #1563ff; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2em; }
        .status-good { color: #28a745; }
        .code-block {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-family: monospace;
            border-left: 4px solid #1563ff;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1><span class="vault-logo">🔐 VAULT</span> PKI Demo - Simplified</h1>
        
        <h2>✅ What's Working</h2>
        <ul>
            <li class="status-good">✅ Vault Agent: Auto-authenticated via AWS EC2</li>
            <li class="status-good">✅ SSL Certificate: Auto-issued from Vault PKI</li>
            <li class="status-good">✅ Apache: Serving HTTPS with Vault certificates</li>
            <li class="status-good">✅ Auto-renewal: Vault Agent handles everything!</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>🎯 Demo Details</h2>
        <p><strong>Domain:</strong> {{ demo_domain }}</p>
        <p><strong>Hostname:</strong> {{ demo_hostname }}.{{ app_domain }}</p>
        <p><strong>Certificate TTL:</strong> {{ cert_max_ttl_h }} hours</p>
        <p><strong>Vault Address:</strong> {{ vault_addr }}</p>

        <h2>🔧 Key Insight</h2>
        <p>This simplified demo shows that <strong>Vault Agent does ALL the work</strong>:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>🔐 Authenticates with AWS EC2 metadata</li>
            <li>📜 Issues SSL certificates from Vault PKI</li>
            <li>🔄 Auto-renews certificates before expiration</li>
            <li>⚡ Restarts Apache when certificates update</li>
            <li>🚫 <strong>No additional watchers needed!</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>💡 Why This is Better</h2>
        <div class="code-block">
        <strong>❌ Complex Approach:</strong>
        Vault Agent + File Watcher + Systemd Path Units + Custom Scripts
        
        <strong>✅ Simple Approach:</strong> 
        Just Vault Agent with template blocks - it handles everything!
        </div>

        <h2>🔍 Check Certificate</h2>
        <div class="code-block">
# View certificate details
openssl x509 -in /etc/httpd/ssl/server.crt -text -noout

# Manual renewal (if needed)
sudo /usr/local/bin/renew-ssl-cert.sh
        </div>

        <p><em>Current time: <span id="time"></span></em></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        setInterval(() => {
            document.getElementById('time').textContent = new Date().toISOString();
        }, 1000);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
